HEADWORD: Seaworthiness
<hw>Sea"wor`thi*ness</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The state or
quality of being seaworthy, or able to resist the ordinary violence of
wind and weather.</def> <rj><au>Kent.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

